<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="269" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[160,1156,886,981]" box="[160,252,886,912]" pageId="4" pageNumber="269">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,252,886,912]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="269">Ecology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[160,1156,886,981]" pageId="4" pageNumber="269">
Found at night on soft bottoms, between 
<taxonomicName box="[642,764,921,946]" class="Florideophyceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ceramiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="269" phylum="Rhodophyta" rank="order">Ceramiales</taxonomicName>
algal species and other red algae. Individuals found during 
<date box="[445,664,956,981]" pageId="4" pageNumber="269" value="2018-04" valueMax="2018-05-31" valueMin="2018-04-00">April and May 2018</date>
were mating.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="269" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="4.[160,1157,1025,1190]" box="[160,300,1025,1051]" pageId="4" pageNumber="269">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,300,1025,1051]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="269">Distribution</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[160,1157,1025,1190]" pageId="4" pageNumber="269">
Japanese coast (
<bibRefCitation author="Pilsbry HA" box="[339,475,1061,1086]" pageId="4" pageNumber="269" pagination="185" refId="ref21806" refString="Pilsbry HA. 1895. Catalogue of the marine shells of Japan with descriptions of new species and notes on others collected by Frederick Stearns. Stearns, Detroit. 8: 185." type="journal article" year="1895">Pilsbry 1895</bibRefCitation>
); 
<collectingCountry box="[493,540,1061,1086]" name="United States of America" pageId="4" pageNumber="269">USA</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hanson D &amp; Cooke S &amp; Hirano Y &amp; Malaquias MAE &amp; Crocetta F &amp; Valdes A" box="[552,757,1061,1086]" pageId="4" pageNumber="269" pagination="77457" refId="ref19945" refString="Hanson D, Cooke S, Hirano Y, Malaquias MAE, Crocetta F, Valdes A. 2013. Slipping through the cracks: the taxonomic impediment conceals the origin and dispersal of Haminoea japonica, an invasive species with impacts to human health. PLoS ONE. 8: e 77457. doi: 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0077457." type="journal article" year="2013">Hanson et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
; GBIF.org 2021); 
<collectingCountry box="[942,989,1061,1086]" name="Italy" pageId="4" pageNumber="269">Italy</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Crocetta F &amp; Macali A &amp; Furfaro G &amp; Cooke S &amp; Villani G &amp; Valdes A" pageId="4" pageNumber="269" pagination="91 - 108" refId="ref18966" refString="Crocetta F, Macali A, Furfaro G, Cooke S, Villani G, Valdes A. 2013. Alien molluscan species established along the Italian shores: an update, with discussions on some Mediterranean alien species categories. ZooKeys. 277: 91 - 108. doi: 10.3897 / zookeys. 277.4362." type="journal article" year="2013">Crocetta et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
); Atlantic Spanish coast: Galicia and Cantabria; Mediterranean Spanish coast: Andalucía (
<bibRefCitation author="Cervera JL &amp; Calado G &amp; Gavaia C &amp; Malaquias MAE &amp; Templado J &amp; Ballesteros M &amp; Megina C &amp; Garcia-Gomez JC" box="[287,507,1130,1155]" pageId="4" pageNumber="269" pagination="5 - 111" refId="ref18631" refString="Cervera JL, Calado G, Gavaia C, Malaquias MAE, Templado J, Ballesteros M, Megina C, Garcia-Gomez JC. 2004. An annotated and updated checklist of the opisthobranchs (Mollusca: Gastropoda) from Spain and Portugal (including Islands and archipelagos). Boletin-Instituto Espanol de Oceanografia. 20: 5 - 111." type="journal article" year="2004">Cervera et al. 2004</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gibson &amp; Chia" authorityYear="1989" box="[550,811,1130,1155]" class="Gastropoda" family="Haminoeidae" genus="Haminoea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cephalaspidea" pageId="4" pageNumber="269" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="cadillegenita">
<emphasis box="[550,811,1130,1155]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="269">Haminoea cadillegenita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); Mediterranean French coast (
<bibRefCitation author="Hanson D &amp; Cooke S &amp; Hirano Y &amp; Malaquias MAE &amp; Crocetta F &amp; Valdes A" box="[166,377,1165,1190]" pageId="4" pageNumber="269" pagination="77457" refId="ref19945" refString="Hanson D, Cooke S, Hirano Y, Malaquias MAE, Crocetta F, Valdes A. 2013. Slipping through the cracks: the taxonomic impediment conceals the origin and dispersal of Haminoea japonica, an invasive species with impacts to human health. PLoS ONE. 8: e 77457. doi: 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0077457." type="journal article" year="2013">Hanson et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
; this study).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="269" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[160,1156,1234,1399]" box="[160,262,1234,1260]" pageId="4" pageNumber="269">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,262,1234,1260]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="269">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[160,1156,1234,1399]" pageId="4" pageNumber="269">
In the marine pools along the French south-eastern Mediterranean coast there are several marine species of Japanese origin, such as the alga wakame [
<taxonomicName authority="(Harvey) Suringar, 1873" authorityName="Suringar" authorityYear="1873" baseAuthorityName="Harvey" class="Phaeophyceae" family="Alariaceae" genus="Undaria" kingdom="Chromista" order="Laminariales" pageId="4" pageNumber="269" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="pinnatifida">
<emphasis box="[843,1055,1304,1329]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="269">Undaria pinnatifida</emphasis>
(Harvey) Suringar, 1873
</taxonomicName>
] and the oyster [
<taxonomicName authority="(Thunberg, 1793)" baseAuthorityName="Thunberg" baseAuthorityYear="1793" box="[510,894,1339,1364]" class="Bivalvia" family="Ostreidae" genus="Magallana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ostreida" pageId="4" pageNumber="269" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="gigas">
<emphasis box="[510,692,1339,1364]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="269">Magallana gigas</emphasis>
(Thunberg, 1793)
</taxonomicName>
], so their presence may be caused by aquaculture (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Faasse M" box="[513,649,1374,1399]" pageId="4" pageNumber="269" pagination="16 - 19" refId="ref19363" refString="Faasse M. 2018. Haminoaea japonica Pilsbry, 1895 (Gastropoda: Cephalaspidea) new to the Netherlands. Spirula. 416: 16 - 19." type="journal article" year="2018">Faasse 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[325,994,1424,1449]" box="[325,994,1424,1449]" pageId="4" pageNumber="269">
Genus 
